Is that enough examples?  This is clearly being done, and with enough frequency that there are many threads on it.<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> The easiest solution to this problem is to simply remove any of the spots where a magician can remain safe while the epic kills a mob.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->Impossible to do without eliminating safe spots in general in zones.  One could increase the number of wanderers, but this would still follow the existing paths.  Increasing the level of the spawn would only increase the level at which it was a viable AFK camp.<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> I got 2 words for this thread:<br>
BE QUIET<br>
Quit trying to get us nerfed<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Verant</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> has repeated stated that first, <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Magicians</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> are overpowered at <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><u>soloing</u><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END-->, and second, that the <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Epic Pet</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> is over powered.<br>
<br>
What can <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Verant</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> mean that we are overpowered in soloing?  Obviously many classes are better at <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><u>ordinary</u><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--> soloing, that is they can reliably take on stronger mobs with less down time.  If we are overpowered, they must be also, yet <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Verant</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> singles out <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Magicians</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->.  Therefore, they cannot be speaking of <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><u>ordinary</u><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--> soloing.  However, possibly barring <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Dire Charm</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->, <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> only <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Epic Magicians</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> can get AFK experience!</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->  Is this unbalanced?  Does it avoid content?  Does it defeat the purpose of the game?  Is it an exploit?<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><u>Look me in the eyes</u><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--> and tell me that <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Verant</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> would not see it that way.  Now tell me that <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Verant</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> will increase the power of pets, so that <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> AFK Experience</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> is <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><u>more</u><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--> effecient, and available in a greater range of spawns.  Oh yes, and that under the present circumstances, <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Verant</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> will make it easier for <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Magicians</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> to acquire your epic.<br>
<br>
Look, we've been tearing our hair out trying to figure out <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><u>why</u><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--> <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Verant</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> thinks we are overpowered at soloing, and that the <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Epic</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> is overpowered.  It can only be <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> AFK Experience</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->.<br>
<br>
Do you have a plan to convince <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Verant</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> that <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> AFK Experience</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> is an acceptable application of <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Risk versus Reward</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> and a <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><u>fair</u><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--> way to play the game?<br>
<br>
Because if you can't, and <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Verant</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> continues to see this as overpowering <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Magicians</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> and the <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Epic</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->, we will never see the utility cap lifted on the <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Epic Pet</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->.  And if the <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Epic Pet</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> is not good enough for raids, we will never see raid-capable pets.<br>
<br>
Attitudes like <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Glenfinen</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->'s are simply selfish.  They would rather keep their little exploit, despite the fact that it holds back the rest of the <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Magician</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> population who do not have their <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Epic</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> or do not take advantage of this <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><u>exploit</u><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END-->.<br>
<br>
On the other hand, if this exploit can be eliminated, it will me <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><u>much</u><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--> easier to argue that <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Magicians</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> are <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><u>not</u><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--> overpowered in soloing, that the <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Epic Pets</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> and our other pets require some increase in power in order to remain viable in the endgame, and that the <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Epic</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> quest should be made somewhat easier.<br>
<br>
While this exploit remains, we have zero chance of getting any of these things.<br>
<br>
As far as keeping quiet, it is far too late.  <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Verant</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> has obviously been aware of this for some time.<br>
